SIMPLE: epicyclical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: epicyclical
<hw>ep`i*cyc"lic*al</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, resembling, or having the motion of,
an epicycle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Epicyclic train</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>a train
of mechanism in which epicyclic motion is involved; esp., a train of
spur wheels, bevel wheels, or belt pulleys, in which an arm, carrying
one or more of the wheels, sweeps around a center lying in an axis
common to the other wheels.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epicycloid</ent>⟦br⟧
